        "last_activity_date": 1400706672,
        "creation_date": 1400706672,
        "body": "<p>In your ContainerReponseFilter, you can do something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class ApplicationResponseFilter implements ContainerResponseFilter {\n\n    @Override\n    public void filter(final ContainerRequestContext request,\n        final ContainerResponseContext response) throws IOException {\n\n        // your code\n        response.getEntity();\n\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>which converts it to your object with JAXB annotations. I was not doing it in my responseFilter, but I've just debugged it and it works.<\/p>\n",
